Yangir are an ancient people known as 'the eastern people'.  They have
long and complex traditions and a unique philosophy and way of living.
The Yangir have an ancient society, based on tradition and differing
ranks of honor. Most of the Yangir adventurers tend to lean towards
the martial arts, since their eastern land is the place where martial 
arts were invented. Many Yangir are monks, practicing their own religion of
self-examination and meditation. They belive in an endless cycle of rebirth.
Yangir are rather small people, the average male is around 155 cm in height
and about 68 kgs in weight. They have an average lifespan of 105 years.
